Faculty Positions

University of California, Irvine
Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences
Tenure-Track/Tenured Faculty Positions
The Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences (ICS) at the University of California, Irvine (UCI), home of the departments of Computer Science, Informatics, and Statistics, is seeking exceptional candidates for multiple tenure/tenured-track faculty positions. See below for open positions or view the UCI Recruit website for all of our academic positions.


School of ICS


Donald Bren Professor in Information and Computer Sciences



Computer Science Department


Open-Rank Faculty Position in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning
Open-Rank Faculty Position in Systems
Open-Rank Faculty Position in Bioinformatics
Professor of Teaching

Informatics Department


Professor of Teaching



Statistics Department


Tenure-Track/Tenured Faculty Position




ICS is one of only five computing-focused schools among the Association of American Universities (AAU) members. The U.S. News and World Report 2018 Best Global Universities ranking identifies UCI as a top 75 university in computer science and one of the top 30 universities for a graduate degree in computer science in the United States. The School’s Informatics Department is internationally renowned for addressing problems at the intersection of people and computing, offering top 10 programs in software engineering, human-computer interaction, and game design. With an emphasis on research in statistical theory and interdisciplinary collaborations, the School’s Statistics Department has grown over the last 20 years to house the Center for Statistical Consulting and was one of the first in the world to offer an undergraduate degree in data science. The School’s 100+ faculty members include 2 NAE Members, 14 ACM Fellows, 10 IEEE Fellows, 9 AAAS Fellows and many other national award winners.

